    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - CUMMINS ISM ENGINE - OPERATION - Brake Switch
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Brake Switch</title>
        <para>The brake switch (5) receives a ground signal on circuits 97-GF, through connector (262) on circuit 97-GA
            from (955). While the brake pedal is released, the switch is closed supplying a ground on circuit 97AL
            through connector (262) to ECM connector (955).
        </para>
        <para>When the brake is applied the ground will be removed signaling the ECM that the brake has been applied.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
